										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2>What Do They Use Sleeknote For?</h2>



<p>Campaign Monitor mainly uses Sleeknote to get people to sign up for their newsletter. At the moment they have 2 types of SleekBoxes active.</p>



<div style="height:60px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h3>1. Guiding Visitors</h3>



<p>The first one is a SleekBox asking their visitors to subscribe to their newsletters. They have decided only to show this SleekBox on their “guides” page with the include/exclude feature that makes them able to choose what pages the SleekBox will be visible on.</p>



<div style="height:20px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="682" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-1024x682.png" alt="campaign-monitor-guide" class="wp-image-94974" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-1024x682.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-300x200.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-768x511.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-380x253.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-600x399.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-760x506.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-53x35.png 53w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-75x50.png 75w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-736x490.png 736w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-220x146.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide-385x256.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/campaign-monitor-guide.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<div style="height:20px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p>When you click on one of the guides, a SleekBox shows up after 15 seconds. They use social proof in the SleekBox as they say “Join over 20,000 other marketers who get actionable tips on improving their email marketing delivered to their inbox”.</p>



<div style="height:60px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h3>2. Collecting Newsletter Subscribers</h3>



<p>The other type of SleekBox they use at the moment is a SleekBox offering an email marketing course. They use this SleekBox on their blog. What they’ve done here, is that they describe what you’ll get when you sign up for their newsletter, which is highly effective to show visitors what they’ll get once they sign up.</p>



<div style="height:20px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p class="has-plum-color has-text-color">CAMPAIGN MONITOR SLEEKBOXES</p>


